      "date": "2021-10-12 17:36:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nArshad, thanks for the review and investigation. I'd used single quotes because I wasn't sure about the nesting of double quotes inside the subshell, but it appears this works as expected (the double quotes around \"$OLDNAME\" are not considered \"end quotes\" for the ones outside $(...)). I also realized that the dirname itself might have a space in it, so that should also be quoted for use. \n\nI've updated the patch, hopefully it can pass this time.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
